<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.825/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-14T13:00:00-05:00">December 14, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 11, 5 p.m. Congress has left to the several States the
                            general power to regulate pilotage. See revised statutes Section
                            4235.</p>
                        <p>Under respective State laws pilotage required in principal United States
                            ports for all vessels engaged in foreign trade.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>